review_blob: This is a smooth and creamy style beer with a moderate head. The aroma is very true to the taste. It leaves a soft and silky taste on the tongue. The deep, rich flavor is the best part, other than the lack of bitterness.
Surprising coffee flavor to this light beer. It has a nice body, not too watery; short and smooth head. There is a subtle bitter after taste but overall a refreshing choice.
beer_name: Stone Stochasticity Project Master of Disguise

review_blob: This is THE beer that turned me into a beer snob! Because its my first REAL beer I have no better review than that but highly recommend this deep and dark beer. Enjoy it slowly!
My favorite part of this beer was the subtle taste of Bourbon Whiskey that lingered after each sip.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Fall Hornin Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Although the head was somewhat lacking, the taste made up for it! There was a perfect balance of bitter, sweet, and smooth taste.
